    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains factory-spec compression across all rotor faces, with a vacuum system that remains leak-free and fully synchronized. The chassis retains its original torsional rigidity, supported by unmolested double-wishbone suspension and the factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Every fluid service is documented, and the five-speed manual transmission delivers crisp, short-throw engagement with no synchro grind. This is a rare opportunity to acquire an FD with zero aftermarket modifications, preserving the precise 50/50 weight distribution and legendary steering feedback that defined the golden era of JDM performance.",
